div#liability-info-step
  // ─── Same wrapper used by other guides (keeps styling consistent) ───
  div.buckets-guide-container
    // ───────── Title & intro ─────────
    h2 📄 Get Your Spreadsheet Ready
    p
      | Before importing your <strong>Liability</strong> data, make sure your
      | spreadsheet includes the following columns&nbsp;(✅&nbsp;required /
      | ⚙️&nbsp;optional):

    // ───────── Checklist ─────────
    ol.guide-steps
      li
        span.step-icon 1️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Client ID (✅)
          |  – ties each loan to the correct client record.
      li
        span.step-icon 2️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Liability Number (✅)
          |  – unique account / loan number.
      li
        span.step-icon 3️⃣
        span.step-text 
          strong Liability Owner Name ⚙️
          |  – Use “Joint” to auto‑assign both owners.
      li
        span.step-icon 4️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Liability Type (⚙️)
          |  – e.g.&nbsp;Vehicle Loan, Home Loan, Personal Loan.
      li
        span.step-icon 4️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Outstanding Balance (⚙️)
          |  – current principal remaining.
      li
        span.step-icon 5️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Creditor Name (⚙️)
          |  – the institution holding the note.
      li
        span.step-icon 6️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Interest Rate % (⚙️)
          |  – annual rate; numbers only or “%” accepted.
      li
        span.step-icon 7️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Monthly Payment (⚙️)
          |  – scheduled payment amount.
      li
        span.step-icon 8️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Estimated Pay‑off Date (⚙️)
          |  – use YYYY‑MM‑DD or MM/DD/YYYY.

    // ───────── Best‑practice tips ─────────
    p.mt-3
      | • Keep Liability Numbers unique but consistent across uploads to avoid duplicates or errors.  
      br
      | • Populate <em>Creditor Name</em> & <em>Interest Rate</em> for more detailed reporting.  
      br
      | • Optional fields can be left blank.
      br
      | • Source data from any CRM, or start with our template below.

    // ───────── Download + Learn‑More links ─────────
    a.import-action-item.d-block.mt-2(
      href='/downloads/liability-import-template.xlsx'
      download
    )
      i.fas.fa-file-download.me-1
      | Download the Liability Import template
    a.import-action-item.learn-more-btn.d-block.mt-2(
      href='#'
      data-video-id='76979871'
      data-bs-toggle='modal'
      data-bs-target='#learnMoreVideoModal'
    )
      i.fas.fa-play-circle.me-1
      | Watch an instructional video (2 min)

    // ───────── Example header row (optional) ─────────
    .example-header.mt-4
      h4 🧪 Example Header Row:
      code Client ID | Liability Number | Liability Owner Name | Liability Type | Outstanding Balance | Creditor Name | Interest Rate % | Monthly Payment | Estimated Pay‑off Date
